### ============================================================
### BTK REIT Management Engine — Full Life Cycle Test Suite
### Version : 1.1.0
### Author  : Rayder-23/BTK
###
### HOW TO USE:
###   1. Ensure the API is running:  dotnet run
###      HTTP  → http://localhost:5039
###   2. Execute each request IN ORDER using the VS Code REST Client
###      extension. Dynamic variables (@name / .response.body) wire
###      IDs automatically — no manual edits needed between steps.
###   3. After the run, execute Scripts/teardown_test_run.sql to
###      remove only the rows created by this suite.
###
### PRE-CONDITIONS (seed data must exist before running):
###   AdminUsers    — user_id=1, status=active
###   Configurations — keys present:
###                    sh_type       → includes 'individual'
###                    status_sh     → includes 'inactive'
###                    transfer_type → includes 'gift'
###                    expense_type  → includes 'management'
###
### IMPORTANT: This suite creates a NEW property each run.
###   The REIT entity (sh_id=1, is_reit=true) must exist in
###   Shareholders as it is the initial 100% owner of every fund.
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5039
@adminId = 1
@reitShId = 1

### ============================================================
### PRE-FLIGHT CHECKS
### Run these first to verify seed data is present.
### Both should return 200 OK with non-empty arrays.
### ============================================================

### PRE-FLIGHT 1 — Confirm admin user exists
# @name preflightAdmin
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/shareholders/{{reitShId}}

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK — REIT entity shareholder (isReit=true) found.
### ✖ If 404: seed the REIT entity before running the suite.
###

### PRE-FLIGHT 2 — Confirm 'sh_type' config key exists
# @name preflightConfig
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/config

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK — array includes entries for sh_type,
###   status_sh, transfer_type, expense_type, status_prop, prop_type.
### ✖ If any key is missing: seed Configurations before running.
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 1 — Register a new Test Shareholder
###
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created
### Captured: shId  →  used in Steps 2, 4a, 8 (failure), portfolio
### ============================================================

# @name registerShareholder
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/shareholders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":       {{adminId}},
  "userName":     "test.ahmed.raza",
  "fullName":     "TEST-RUN Ahmed Raza",
  "contactNo":    "+92-300-1234567",
  "contactEmail": "test.ahmed.raza@btkreit.test",
  "shType":       "individual",
  "cnic":         "35202-9988776-1",
  "isOverseas":   false,
  "isFiller":     false,
  "isReit":       false
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created
###   { "shId": N, "userName": "test.ahmed.raza", "fullName": "TEST-RUN Ahmed Raza" }
###
### @capture  shId = registerShareholder.response.body.shId
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 2 — Add a Bank Account to the new Shareholder
###
### Route: POST /api/shareholders/account  (shId goes in the body)
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created
### Captured: shAccountId  →  referenced in teardown
### ============================================================

# @name addBankAccount
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/shareholders/account
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shId":         {{registerShareholder.response.body.shId}},
  "bank":         "HBL",
  "accountTitle": "TEST-RUN Ahmed Raza",
  "acNo":         "PK36HABB0000009988776602",
  "userId":       {{adminId}},
  "notes":        "TEST-RUN bank account"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created
###   { "shAccountId": N, "shId": N, "bank": "HBL", "acNo": "...", "status": "active" }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 3 — Onboard a Property (creates Property + TrustFund + FundDetail)
###
### Creates a brand-new property each run — no dependency on a
### pre-existing prop_id. REIT entity takes 100% ownership at inception.
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created
### Captured: propId, fundId, fundDtId (seed ownership row)
### ============================================================

# @name onboardProperty
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/properties/onboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":        {{adminId}},
  "propType":      "commercial",
  "propName":      "TEST-RUN BTK Commerce Tower",
  "address":       "Plot 14, Blue Area, Constitution Avenue",
  "city":          "Islamabad",
  "provinceState": "ICT",
  "country":       "Pakistan",
  "purchasePrice": 50000000.00,
  "currentValue":  55000000.00,
  "status":        "active",
  "fundTitle":     "TEST-RUN BTK Commerce Fund",
  "fundTotalValue": 50000000.00,
  "propNotes":     "TEST-RUN property — safe to delete after test",
  "fundNotes":     "TEST-RUN fund — safe to delete after test"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created
###   { "propId": N, "propName": "TEST-RUN BTK Commerce Tower",
###     "fundId": N, "fundTotalValue": 50000000, "fundDtId": N }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 4a — Initiate a 10% Share Transfer (gift: REIT → Ahmed Raza)
###
### Using transfer_type='gift' avoids the payment body requirement,
### keeping the lifecycle test self-contained.
### Route returns 200 OK (not 201).
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK
### Captured: transferId  →  used in Step 4b
### ============================================================

# @name initiateTransfer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/transfers/initiate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":       {{adminId}},
  "fundId":       {{onboardProperty.response.body.fundId}},
  "fromShId":     {{reitShId}},
  "toShId":       {{registerShareholder.response.body.shId}},
  "transferType": "gift",
  "pctTransfer":  10.00,
  "notes":        "TEST-RUN: Initial 10% gift from REIT to Ahmed Raza"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK
###   { "transferId": N, "status": "pending", "message": "Transfer initiated..." }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 4b — Complete the Transfer
###
### userId is a QUERY PARAM — no request body required for gift transfers.
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK  |  verifiedTotalPct = 100.00
### ============================================================

# @name completeTransfer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/transfers/complete/{{initiateTransfer.response.body.transferId}}?userId={{adminId}}

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK
###   { "transferId": N, "buyerFundDtId": N, "sellerFundDtId": N,
###     "verifiedTotalPct": 100.00, "message": "Transfer completed..." }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 5a — Record Rental Income  (April 2026)
###
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created  |  status = "overdue" (initial state)
### Captured: rentId  →  used in Step 5b, 6a
### ============================================================

# @name recordRental
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rental/record
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":    {{adminId}},
  "fundId":    {{onboardProperty.response.body.fundId}},
  "rentMonth": 4,
  "rentYear":  2026,
  "dueDate":   "2026-04-30",
  "amountDue": 250000.00,
  "notes":     "TEST-RUN: April 2026 rental income"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created
###   { "rentId": N, "fundId": N, "rentMonth": 4, "rentYear": 2026,
###     "amountDue": 250000, "amountPaid": 0, "lateFee": 0, "status": "overdue" }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 5b — Receive Rental Payment (full settlement)
###
### Route: PATCH /api/rental/receive-payment/{rentId}
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK  |  status = "paid"
### ============================================================

# @name receiveRental
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/rental/receive-payment/{{recordRental.response.body.rentId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":      {{adminId}},
  "amountPaid":  250000.00,
  "lateFee":     0.00,
  "paymentDate": "2026-04-28",
  "notes":       "TEST-RUN: Full April 2026 rent received"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK
###   { "rentId": N, "amountDue": 250000, "amountPaid": 250000,
###     "lateFee": 0, "status": "paid" }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 6a — Calculate Dividends  (10% tax rate)
###
### Ahmed Raza owns 10% → gross = 25,000 / tax = 2,500 / net = 22,500
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK  |  dividendsCreated = 1
### Captured: dividendIds[0]  →  used in Step 6b
### ============================================================

# @name calculateDividends
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/dividend/calculate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":    {{adminId}},
  "fundId":    {{onboardProperty.response.body.fundId}},
  "rentMonth": 4,
  "rentYear":  2026,
  "taxRate":   0.10,
  "notes":     "TEST-RUN: April 2026 dividend calculation"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK
###   { "dividendsCreated": 1, "dividendIds": [N], "taxRate": 0.10, ... }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 6b — Confirm Dividend Payout
###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK  |  status = "paid", paymentMethod = "bank-transfer"
### ============================================================

# @name confirmDividend
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/dividend/confirm-payout/{{calculateDividends.response.body.dividendIds[0]}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": {{adminId}},
  "notes":  "TEST-RUN: Bank transfer confirmed — April 2026"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK
###   { "divId": N, "status": "paid", "paymentMethod": "bank-transfer",
###     "paidOn": "2026-...", "netAmountPaid": 22500 }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 7a — Record a Management Expense
###
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created  |  status = "pending"
### Captured: expenseId  →  used in Step 7b and failure test
### ============================================================

# @name recordExpense
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/expense/record
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":      {{adminId}},
  "fundId":      {{onboardProperty.response.body.fundId}},
  "month":       4,
  "year":        2026,
  "expenseType": "mgmt-fee",
  "description": "TEST-RUN: Monthly management fee - April 2026",
  "amount":      12500.00,
  "notes":       "TEST-RUN: Standard 5% management fee"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 201 Created
###   { "expenseId": N, "fundId": N, "expenseType": "management",
###     "amount": 12500, "status": "pending" }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 7b — Settle the Expense
###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK  |  status = "paid"
### ============================================================

# @name settleExpense
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/expense/settle/{{recordExpense.response.body.expenseId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": {{adminId}},
  "notes":  "TEST-RUN: Management fee paid via bank transfer"
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK
###   { "expenseId": N, "status": "paid", ... }
###


### ============================================================
### STEP 8 — Verify Audit Log
###
### Filter by the fund created in this run to isolate test entries.
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK  |  ≥ 10 entries for this test run
### ============================================================

# @name auditLogFull
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/log/recent?limit=50

###
### ✔ Expected: Most-recent 50 log entries — test actions appear at top.
###

### STEP 8b — Audit scoped to ShareholderID from Step 1
# @name auditByShareholder
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/log/recent?userId={{adminId}}&limit=20

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK — entries authored by adminId=1 from this run.
###

### STEP 8c — Fund Summary health check
# @name fundSummary
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Fund/{{onboardProperty.response.body.fundId}}/summary

###
### ✔ Expected: 200 OK
###   latestRental.status = "paid"
###   expenses.totalPaid  > 0
###   activeOwners.length = 2 (REIT @ 90%, Ahmed Raza @ 10%)
###


### ============================================================
### FAILURE / VALIDATION TESTS
###
### These MUST return 4xx to confirm guardrails are active.
### Run these after the lifecycle steps so all IDs are populated.
### ============================================================

### ── FAILURE 1: Invalid shareholder status ──────────────────────
### Expects: 400 Bad Request
### Proves:  ValidationService rejects values outside 'status_sh' list
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name failInvalidShareholderStatus
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/shareholders/{{registerShareholder.response.body.shId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "abandoned",
  "userId": {{adminId}}
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 400 Bad Request
###   { "error": "Invalid value", "field": "status", "allowed": [...] }
###

### ── FAILURE 2: Invalid expense type ────────────────────────────
### Expects: 400 Bad Request
### Proves:  ValidationService rejects values outside 'expense_type' list
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name failInvalidExpenseType
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/expense/record
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":      {{adminId}},
  "fundId":      {{onboardProperty.response.body.fundId}},
  "month":       4,
  "year":        2026,
  "expenseType": "bribery",
  "description": "TEST-RUN: This should be rejected",
  "amount":      99.99
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 400 Bad Request
###   { "error": "Invalid value", "field": "expense_type", "allowed": [...] }
###

### ── FAILURE 3: Duplicate dividend calculation ───────────────────
### Expects: 409 Conflict
### Proves:  Idempotency guard on dividend calculation
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name failDuplicateDividend
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/dividend/calculate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":    {{adminId}},
  "fundId":    {{onboardProperty.response.body.fundId}},
  "rentMonth": 4,
  "rentYear":  2026,
  "taxRate":   0.10
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 409 Conflict
###   "Dividend rows already exist for FundID N, period 4/2026."
###

### ── FAILURE 4: Settle an already-paid expense ──────────────────
### Expects: 400 Bad Request
### Proves:  Double-settle guard on Expenses
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name failDoubleSettle
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/expense/settle/{{recordExpense.response.body.expenseId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": {{adminId}}
}

###
### ✔ Expected: 400 Bad Request
###   "Expense expense_id=N is already marked 'paid'."
###

### ── FAILURE 5: Complete an already-completed transfer ───────────
### Expects: 400 Bad Request
### Proves:  Status guard on transfer completion
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name failDoubleComplete
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/transfers/complete/{{initiateTransfer.response.body.transferId}}?userId={{adminId}}

###
### ✔ Expected: 400 Bad Request
###   "Transfer ID N has status 'completed' and cannot be completed."
###


### ============================================================
### END OF TEST SUITE
###
### Expected summary after a clean run:
###   Lifecycle (Steps 1–8c): ALL 2xx
###   Failure tests (1–5)   : ALL 4xx (400 or 409)
###   Audit log              : ≥ 10 entries for this test run
###
### To clean up: run Scripts/teardown_test_run.sql
### ============================================================
